		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>RetroGEN, Sega Genesis to SNES adapter</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I just saw this new product at Tototek. Apparently, this thing let you play Genesis cart on a SNES. I suppose it work in a similar fashion as the old Tristar adapter, most likely use a Genesis-on-a-chip clone and highjack the SNES controller signal. Anybody tried it? Sound kinda stupid to me since you still need to hook up composite cable to the adapter and not to the SNES.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
